Today I have learned that one of your agents scammed/ conned/ mislead, however which way you want to call it , my entire family. He sold my husband policies for my children , ages 8 and 3 yrs , and told him that we " needed" this policy as it was a great investment for our children's futures. To kind of look at it like a savings account gaining intrest, and that after 5 , yes (five) years , it would pay for itself and have a great cash value. 
How could someone sell a life insurance policy to create an investment for your future? As it only pays upon death. 
Now we have wasted unnecessary funds, that could've been placed into a real savings account for them!
Why would someone mislead a "client" like so? Well... We were what he needed to get over his selling/ commission mark , as he was a newhire, and he was willing to tell anyone anything to put some money in his pocket! And on top of all of this, when I told him I wanted to cancel the policy, for multiple reasons(too many to list, mostly bc he was an uneducated agent whom never had any logical answers, other than, ill get back to you, and never doing so.) Then he felt the need to use social media to blast myself and my family, for ruining his paycheck! How can your employees get away with such ? Not to mention it was completely unethical how he went about this! Who can I contact of higher authority regarding this issue?

Long ago in the mid seventies, myself and my friend chris cook were skateboarding. we rode off the sidewalk curb one right after another. i made it into the parking lot still skating, however chris fell and broke his wrist, a compound fracture which is when the bone breaks in half and protrudes the body. chris' wrist was on top of his arm. i'm sure glad his mom was off work that day and able to get him to the hospital so he could be repaired. oh, i'm not suggesting that anyone shouldn't benefit from the world's strongest government where food stamps and medical attention are involved. though mitt romney believes that chris shouldn't have received medical attention or lunch that day had his parents not made enough money for those things. chris is now a strong and healthy man. though had he been turned away at the hospital that day back when we were about 14 years old he wouldn't have a left hand on his body.
